The [5 carat emerald cut diamond ring](/5-carat-emerald-cut-diamond-ring) has two completely different price tags depending on one decision. In natural diamonds, a GIA-certified 5ct emerald cut starts at [$121,475](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/16360919?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and goes to [$251,745](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/18249190?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) in current certified market data.

In lab-grown, an [IGI 5.11ct E-VVS1 emerald cut costs $8,210](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28857918?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). Add an [$860 solitaire setting](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/ten-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-311235?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) and the complete ring is $9,070.

This page covers natural and lab 5ct emerald cut diamond ring prices, the settings that work best at this size, and the full price range for 6ct through 10ct. Stone plus setting equals ring — both costs are here, with complete ring totals for every option in the tables and Final Verdict. For the stone-only guide without settings, see the [loose emerald cut diamond guide](/loose-emerald-cut-diamond).

---

**TL;DR**

- Natural 5ct emerald cut: cheapest GIA stone is [5.00ct D-VS1 at **$121,475**](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/16360919?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
- Lab 5ct emerald cut: entry point is [IGI 5.11ct E-VVS1 at **$8,210**](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28857918?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
- Ring setting: solitaire from [$860 (14K white gold)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/ten-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-14k-white-gold-by-james-allen-item-311235?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) to [$4,625 (platinum bezel)](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/bezel-set-emerald-cut-side-stone-diamond-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-304637?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)
- Complete lab 5ct ring: from **$9,070** (stone + setting)
- Complete natural 5ct ring: from **$122,335** (stone + setting)
- Size: approximately 12mm × 9mm — covers the full finger width
- 7ct natural: [GIA 7.01ct D-VS1 at $392,388](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/19301085?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational); 7ct lab: [IGI 7.27ct F-VVS1 at $10,079](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27540861?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational)

→ Best value 5ct ring: [IGI 5.11ct E-VVS1 lab + 14K white gold solitaire = **$9,070 complete**](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28857918?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational). E-VVS1 at 5ct is a better grade than any natural 5ct stone available under $200K. At $9,070 for a complete ring, the 5ct emerald cut is accessible in lab at a price that would buy a 1ct natural.

Priority: if origin matters, budget $125,000 minimum for the stone alone. If presence on the hand matters, lab delivers a bigger, better-graded stone at 7% of the natural price.

