The jump from 3ct to 5ct in an emerald cut is visible immediately in a side-by-side comparison. From 3ct (10.5mm × 8mm) to 5ct (12mm × 9mm), both dimensions grow by 1.5mm. At arm's length, that 1.5mm per dimension changes the stone from prominent to commanding.

The L/W ratio at 5ct matters exactly the same as at 2ct. The 1.29–1.35 range is classic. Confirm exact millimeter measurements before buying — "5ct emerald cut" describes weight, not the specific shape character of any individual stone.

