## 6, 7, 8, and 10 Carat Emerald Cut Diamond Ring

The semantic keywords in this post range from 5ct all the way to 10ct and 20ct. Here is what current certified market data shows for each size.

**6 Carat Emerald Cut Diamond Ring**

No GIA-certified natural 6ct emerald cut diamonds appear in current certified market inventory. At this weight, natural stones are private-sale items — they trade through auction houses and specialist dealers, not standard retail listings. Based on the 5ct to 7ct price progression in natural, a 6ct in D-VS1 or comparable grades would be expected to price between $250,000 and $380,000.

A 6ct emerald cut measures approximately 13mm × 9.5mm — visibly larger than 5ct, though not as dramatic a jump as 3ct to 5ct. For lab, 6ct does not appear as a standard listing — source through a specialist dealer who can search broader inventory than standard certified retail.

**7 Carat Emerald Cut Diamond Ring**

Two GIA-certified natural 7ct emerald cut diamonds are in current certified market inventory.

