At 7ct, the emerald cut measures approximately 14mm × 10.5mm. That is a length that nearly spans the full finger on an average hand. At this size, the stone is unmistakably present at any distance.

The two natural 7ct stones represent a $123,206 spread for a D color difference: D-VS1 at $392,388 versus D-FL at $515,594. The grade that is unaffordable in a natural 2ct stone ($60,000+ for D-FL) is still $515,000 at 7ct. In lab, the [7.27ct F-VVS1 at $10,079](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/27540861?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is 97% less than the natural D-VS1 equivalent at the same carat weight. The complete 7ct lab ring with a [platinum solitaire at $1,200](https://www.bluenile.com/engagement-rings/design-your-own-ring/ten-prong-solitaire-engagement-ring-in-platinum-by-james-allen-item-311240?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is $11,279.

**8 Carat Emerald Cut Diamond Ring**

No certified natural 8ct emerald cut diamonds appear in current inventory. Natural 8ct emerald cuts are true collector stones — expect prices above $500,000 for any GIA-certified natural 8ct in D-VS1 or better. At 8ct (approximately 14.8mm × 11mm), lab prices run roughly $11,000–$12,000 based on the 7.27ct at $10,079 and 9.53ct at $13,212 in current certified lab data.

**10 Carat Emerald Cut Diamond Ring**

A natural 10ct emerald cut diamond ring is a fine-jewelry rarity — these stones don't appear in standard retail inventory and price from approximately $1,000,000 upward depending on grade. They trade through private channels, auction houses, and high-end dealers who specialize in exceptional stones. In lab, the [IGI 9.53ct F-VVS1 at $13,212](https://www.bluenile.com/diamond-details/28842463?a_aid=69d7c31a91b8d&a_cid=55e51e63&chan=blog-informational) is the best available reference point. A 10ct lab emerald cut would price approximately $14,000–$16,000 for the stone, with a complete ring under $17,000 using a solitaire setting.

At 10ct, the emerald cut reaches approximately 16.5mm × 12mm — the stone nearly spans the entire width of the finger. This is as close as any ring gets to a red-carpet showpiece in wearable daily jewelry.

